  "issue_number": 11,
  "issue_title": "Approve Writes Artifact Before Moving Proposal",
  "issue_body": "**Location:** `src/vouch/proposals.py:235-271`\n\n`approve()` writes the durable artifact (e.g. `put_claim`) before updating the proposal status to `APPROVED` via `move_proposal_to_decided`. If the process crashes between the two operations, the proposal remains `PENDING` while the artifact is already on disk. A second approval call would then write a duplicate or silently overwrite with different metadata.\n\n### Suggested fix\n\nCheck for artifact existence before writing (idempotent guard), or update proposal status first.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-19T22:47:07.000Z",
